						<div class="postbody">In practice, only if there are peripherals that care only that a read happened. In the NES/FC, that includes $2002, $2007, $4016, and $4017, but not much else.<br /><br />In the 2600, only the bankswitching registers count. I guess that means you could deliberately trigger a bankswitch that would then fall over into a read from the RAM portion of the RIOT?<br /><br />I don't think the C64 or VIC-20 do anything in response to just a read... It looks like some of the Apple 2 I/O registers do.</div>

